    "text": "Erdős Problem #724: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $f(n)$ be the maximum number of mutually orthogonal Latin squares of order $n$. Is it true that\\[f(n) \\gg n^{1/2}?\\] Current best: Euler conjectured that $f(n)=1$ when $n\\equiv 2\\pmod{4}$, but this was disproved by Bose, Parker, and Shrikhande \\cite{BPS60} who proved $f(n)\\geq 2$ for $n\\geq 7$. Prize: no. OEIS: A001438. Tags: combinatorics.",
